When adding a new method:
 - implement it
 - edit lib/extensions/all.rb if a new file was introduced
 - edit ChangeLog (include version number)
 - edit VERSION
 - regenerate documentation (check doco for new method looks OK)
 - commit and tag with new (teeny) version
   - check what you're committing first with cvs -n up
   - use ChangeLog entry as commit comment
 - upload RDoc to website


When releasing a new version:
 - update webpage with release information and method list
 - create ChangeLog entry to mark new release
 - commit and tag everything to new level
 - create tgz to release on RubyForge
